Rházes Hernández López (1918-1991) was a Venezuelan composer and flutist born in Caracas June 30, 1918.
He composed several works for the piano, including Casualismo no. 6 (1984), and Prisma no. 1 (1979).
He composed several works for the piano, including Casualismo no. 6 (1984), and Prisma no. 1 (1979).
The latter was performed at the Third Music Festival of Caracas, Venezuela (1966) by violinist Jose Figueroa, cellist Adolfo Odnoposoff, and pianist Hector Tosar.
He composed at least one work for string orchestra, his Las torres desprevenidas (1990).
